# Website module conventions

## API clients (`src/api/`)

- One file per product area (`sos.js`, `mental.js`, `generic.js`, `reports.js`).
- Build URLs with `*Url()` helpers from `src/config/api.js` — never hardcode staging hosts in pages.
- Normalize nested API envelopes once in the client; pages should receive clean arrays/objects.
- Export small helpers (fallbacks, fee math, image URL) next to the client when RN has them.

## Pages (`src/pages/<module>/`)

- Shared chrome in `*Shell.jsx` (back, title, optional header actions).
- Flow state in context or `sessionStorage` (see `MentalHealthContext`, `GenericMedicineContext`).
- Loading / empty / error states required for list screens.
- Deep links must match routes registered under `/app/<module>/...`.

## Do not

```jsx
// ❌ Marketing ModulePage stub for a shipped app feature
<Route path="sos" element={<ModulePage />} />

// ✅ Real module home
<Route path="sos" element={<SosHome />} />
```

```js
// ❌ Absolute API host in a page
fetch("https://staging.setuai.com/mental/api/v1/submissions")

// ✅ Config + client
import { fetchSubmissions } from "../../api/mental"
await fetchSubmissions(session)
```
